<div id="tab_plugin_octogoat" class="tab-pane">
    <div class="container-fluid octogoat-ui">

        <div class="octogoat-hero">
            <img class="octogoat-hero-art"
                 src="/plugin/octogoat/static/img/octogoat_hero.jpg"
                 alt="OctoGOAT hero art">
        </div>

        <div class="octogoat-moonraker-control-row">
            <label class="octogoat-moonraker-toggle"
                   title="Moonraker/Klipper easy connect in octogoat settings with your printer's local IP ex 192.168.1.you know">
                <input type="checkbox"
                       data-bind="checked: moonrakerMode, event: { change: setControlModeFromToggle }">
                Moonraker/Klipper Mode:
                <strong data-bind="text: moonrakerModeLabel"></strong>
            </label>

            <button class="btn octogoat-moonraker-test-btn"
                    type="button"
                    data-bind="click: testMoonraker"
                    title="Test Moonraker connection using the URL and API key in OctoGoat settings.">
                Test Connection
            </button>
        </div>

        <div class="octogoat-nav-row">
            <div class="octogoat-nav-left">
                <button class="btn octogoat-nav-btn"
                        type="button"
                        data-toggle="modal"
                        data-target="#pricing-modal"
                        title="place holder">
                    Path to saving time, $ and your failed print
                </button>

                <button class="btn octogoat-nav-btn"
                        type="button"
                        data-toggle="modal"
                        data-target="#howto-modal"
                        title="place holder">
                    How it works
                </button>

                <button class="btn octogoat-nav-btn"
                        type="button"
                        data-toggle="modal"
                        data-target="#contact-modal"
                        title="the_real_octogoat@proton.me">
                    Contact
                </button>
            </div>

            <div class="octogoat-nav-right">
                <span class="label label-success"
                      data-bind="visible: licenseValid()">
                    License Valid
                </span>

                <span class="label label-important"
                      data-bind="visible: !licenseValid()">
                    License Required
                </span>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="octogoat-card">
            <div class="octogoat-inputs-head">
                <h4>Select the GCODE file of the print to be saved</h4>

                <div class="octogoat-file-selector">
                    <div class="octogoat-file-selector-label">You are about to save:</div>

                    <div class="octogoat-file-selected"
                         data-bind="text: selectedFileLabel"
                         title="place holder"></div>

                    <div class="octogoat-file-selector-controls">
                        <select class="input-block-level octogoat-input"
                                data-bind="
                                    options: availableFiles,
                                    optionsText: 'label',
                                    optionsValue: 'path',
                                    value: selectedServerFilePath,
                                    optionsCaption: 'Choose OctoPrint file',
                                    event: { change: selectServerFile }
                                "
                                title="place holder"></select>

                        <button class="btn octogoat-function-btn octogoat-file-picker-btn"
                                type="button"
                                data-bind="click: openLocalFilePicker"
                                title="place holder">
                            Choose From Device
                        </button>
                    </div>

                    <div class="octogoat-file-dropzone"
                         data-bind="css: { 'is-dragging': isDraggingFile() }"
                         title="place holder">
                        Drag and drop a `.gcode` file here
                    </div>

                    <input id="octogoat-local-file-input"
                           type="file"
                           accept=".gcode,.gco,.gc,.g"
                           class="octogoat-hidden-file-input">
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="row-fluid">
                <div class="span6">
                    <label>Measured Print Height (mm)</label>

                    <input type="number"
                           step="0.1"
                           class="input-block-level octogoat-input"
                           placeholder="22.0"
                           data-bind="value: measuredHeight"
                           title="Measure the partial print on the left and right side and enter the lower value to the nearest 0.1 mm.">
                </div>

                <div class="span6">
                    <label>Alignment Side</label>

                    <select class="input-block-level octogoat-input"
                            data-bind="value: alignmentSide"
                            title="Choose which side of the print had the lowest value">
                        <option value="left">Left</option>
                        <option value="right">Right</option>
                    </select>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="octogoat-help-text">
                Layer height is detected automatically from the selected GCODE file.
            </div>

            <button class="btn btn-large btn-block octogoat-action-btn"
                    data-bind="click: buildResume, enable: licenseValid() && !buildInProgress()"
                    title="Reconstruct safe resume GCODE using the selected file and measured height.">
                Click here for your safe _resume.GCODE and to begin precision alignment
            </button>
        </div>

        <div class="octogoat-card" data-bind="visible: buildInProgress() || resumeBuilt()">
            <div class="octogoat-warning-box">
                <div class="octogoat-warning-intro" data-bind="visible: buildInProgress()">
                    Your safe _resume.GCODE is being calculated, This may take a few seconds.
                    <br><br>
                </div>
                While waiting let's talk about the different ways to get your nozzle lined up to the print.
                3 ways to start. 
                 First one, if you run Marlin your machine may still be holding its coordinate state. Makes this easy af.
                Since for this first step we don't need perfect, just a safe ballpark, we get more precise than homing 
                on the next step so if your printer has held on to coordinate state all you need to do is check that
                first box under "safe resume homing". *DO NOT TRUST THE GREYED OUUT COORDINATES IN FLUIDD/MAINSAIL FOR THIS*
                  Second way: If you know or find out the coords. where your printer parks when you cancel_print, then 
                you can enter those coords. in octogoat settings and save them. They will be displayed under "safe resume homing"
                as your "assumed position" coords. Then you just click that second checkbox and octogoat will tell your printer 
                that is where you are. 
                *Don't tell nobody but if you are confident in your machines "assumed position" or its current coordinant state, 
                you can skip the precision alignment and just set temps and hit resume now and go back to bed. 
                  The last option is the easy fail safe "safe resume homing" which simply homes x and y and sets a temporary "safe_z"
                  
                    However you begin on the next step, when you hit that next button ocotgoat then moves the toolhead to the 
                "true alignment point".  From there you use your motion commands to algn nozzle to that perfect left or 
                right-most edge, and drop it down to paper-test perfect.  Then when you hit "position calibrated" Octogoat informs 
                your printer of absolute coordinate reality, triangulating your printer to the partial print and to the newly 
                constructed safe _resume.GCODE.  Way easier done than said. If your a noob or have any questions holler at me, 
                I got you. Looks like your code is ready now.
                
                    Let's get you lined back up and watch this thing resume like it never missed a beat!
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="octogoat-card" data-bind="visible: resumeBuilt()">
            <div class="octogoat-stage-header">
                <h4>Calibrate Position</h4>

                <div class="octogoat-datum-display"
                     title="once lined up and locked in, this becomes absolute true coordinate reality">
                    True Alignment Point:
                    <span>X=<strong data-bind="text: datumX"></strong></span>
                    <span>Y=<strong data-bind="text: datumY"></strong></span>
                    <span>Z=<strong data-bind="text: datumZ"></strong></span>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="row-fluid">
                <div class="span6">
                    <button class="btn btn-block octogoat-function-btn"
                            data-bind="click: openSafeResumeHomingPrompt"
                            title="Choose Safe Resume Homing, attest the current coordinates, or use saved assumed position coordinates.">
                        1 - Safe Resume Homing
                    </button>
                </div>

                <div class="span6">
                    <button class="btn btn-block octogoat-function-btn"
                            data-bind="click: goToDatum"
                            title="this moves nozzle overtop and close to the precision alignment point.">
                        2 - On to Precision Alignment
                    </button>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="octogoat-card" data-bind="visible: resumeBuilt()">
            <h4>Resume GCODE Preview</h4>

            <pre class="octogoat-preview"
                 data-bind="visible: resumeBuilt(), text: previewText"></pre>
        </div>

        <div class="octogoat-card octogoat-resume-card">
            <label class="checkbox octogoat-checkbox">
                <input type="checkbox"
                       data-bind="checked: motionAcknowledged">

                I acknowledge toolhead has been aligned, nozzle temp is correct and it is safe to move
            </label>

            <div class="octogoat-resume-actions">
                <button class="btn btn-large octogoat-download-btn"
                        data-bind="enable: canDownloadResume(), click: downloadResume"
                        title="place holder">
                    Download Resume GCODE
                </button>

                <button class="btn btn-large octogoat-resume-btn"
                        data-bind="enable: canResume(), click: resumeNow"
                        title="Your print resumes immediately unless adjusted in octogoat settings! make sure temps are set!">
                    Resume Print
                </button>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="octogoat-legal-links">
            <a href="https://app.lazarus3dprint.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Terms</a>
            <span aria-hidden="true">|</span>
            <a href="https://app.lazarus3dprint.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Privacy</a>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div id="pricing-modal"
         class="modal hide fade"
         tabindex="-1"
         role="dialog"
         aria-labelledby="pricing-modal-label"
         aria-hidden="true">
        <div class="modal-header">
            <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-hidden="true">&times;</button>
            <h3 id="pricing-modal-label">Activate OctoGOAT</h3>
        </div>

        <div class="modal-body">
            <p>Choose a plan to activate OctoGOAT.</p>
            <div id="pricing-table-container"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="modal-footer">
            <button class="btn" type="button" data-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div id="safe-resume-homing-modal"
         class="modal hide fade"
         tabindex="-1"
         role="dialog"
         aria-labelledby="safe-resume-homing-modal-label"
         aria-hidden="true">
        <div class="modal-header">
            <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-hidden="true">&times;</button>
            <h3 id="safe-resume-homing-modal-label">Safe Resume Homing</h3>
        </div>

        <div class="modal-body">
            <div class="octogoat-option-stack">
                <label class="checkbox octogoat-checkbox octogoat-expert-option"
                       title="This option is mostly for Marlin users whose printer has not lost it's coordinate state. Klipper drops cooordinate state after a cancel printe even (greyed out coordinates in Fluidd/ mainsail UI will not work).">
                    <input type="checkbox" data-bind="checked: attestCurrentCoordinates">
                    My printer already has a current coordinate state. (not for Klipper as greyed out coordinates are not established or trustworthy)
                </label>

                <label class="checkbox octogoat-checkbox octogoat-expert-option"
                       title="Use saved assumed position coordinates from OctoGoat settings. If your printer is at a known parking place, such as cancel_print, you can save those coordinates in octogoat settings and by checking the box octogoat will tell your printer where it is. (For my Klipper people)">
                    <input type="checkbox" data-bind="checked: useAssumedPositionCoordinates">
                    Use assumed position coordinates
                </label>

                <div class="octogoat-datum-display"
                     title="Coordinates currently saved in OctoGoat settings for the assumed position option.">
                    Saved Assumed Position:
                    <span>X=<strong data-bind="text: parkX"></strong></span>
                    <span>Y=<strong data-bind="text: parkY"></strong></span>
                    <span>Z=<strong data-bind="text: parkZ"></strong></span>
                </div>

                <div class="octogoat-standard-option">
                    <div class="octogoat-standard-label">Standard start</div>
                    <button class="btn btn-large btn-block octogoat-action-btn"
                            type="button"
                            data-bind="click: applySafeResumeHoming"
                            title="Does a normal homing of X and Y and temporarily sets a fake z for a high number until true z is established in next step.">
                        Safe Resume Homing
                    </button>
                    <p class="octogoat-disclaimer"
                       title="Oddball printer? Unsure if safe to home x and y with print on the bed? Test beforehand while bed is clear with this command [G28 X Y].">
                       Safe for most all common cartesian/corexy printers
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="modal-footer">
            <button class="btn" type="button" data-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div id="alignment-step-modal"
         class="modal hide fade"
         tabindex="-1"
         role="dialog"
         aria-labelledby="alignment-step-modal-label"
         aria-hidden="true">
        <div class="modal-header">
            <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-hidden="true">&times;</button>
            <h3 id="alignment-step-modal-label">Move on to precision alignment</h3>
        </div>

        <div class="modal-body">
            <p class="octogoat-critical-warning">
                <strong>Very important:</strong> Do not use Z offset toggles to align Z. This throws off
                the bed mesh and the resume will fail and may cause a crash. Also be careful not to press
                the home all button positioned very close to the Z motion controller in Fluidd / Mainsail.
                If you do, it happens, don't panic. Kill power or emergency stop and begin again. No big 
                deal. Also highly recommend to never use printer's touchpad.. ever.. especially for motion.
                (It can get weird when it comes to mottion control on a touchpad).
            </p>

            <div class="octogoat-failsafe-row">
                <button class="btn octogoat-failsafe-btn"
                        type="button"
                        data-bind="click: resetAlignmentZ"
                        title="For Klipper this sends SET_KINEMATIC_POSITION Z=200 SET_HOMED=Z. For Marlin this sends G92 Z200.">
                    Out of bounds error? Need more room to align Z?... press here
                </button>
            </div>

            <div class="octogoat-calibrated-action">
                <p>
                    Once nozzle is aligned to left/right most edge within a paper test of the top of the print press here
                </p>
                <button class="btn btn-large btn-block octogoat-function-btn"
                        type="button"
                        data-bind="click: lockDatum"
                        title="Once you are perfectly aligned hitting this button will lock in true coordinate postiton then followed by a safe z hop so you can warm up your nozzle without melting the print.">
                    Position Calibrated
                </button>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="modal-footer">
            <button class="btn" type="button" data-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div id="howto-modal"
         class="modal hide fade"
         tabindex="-1"
         role="dialog"
         aria-labelledby="howto-modal-label"
         aria-hidden="true">
        <div class="modal-header">
            <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-hidden="true">&times;</button>
            <h3 id="howto-modal-label">How To</h3>
        </div>

        <div class="modal-body">
            <p>Super easy workflow even your first time, even if not experienced.  After you have went through checkout to recieve your 
            share in billions of dollars worth of savings simply upload the file of the print that failed. Use your calipers to measure
            the left and right side, note which is shorter, enter that measurment to the nearest 0.1mm Don't sweat it too much, (the tolerance is = to layer height) 
            Ocotgoat will find the exact layer of failure as long as you are within the tolerance. Then pick which side that measurement came from
            the left or right.  Hard part is over.  Now click the big button to get your safe _resume.GCODE and follow the simple alignment button 
            instructions.  We have multiple ways for everyone to get lined up with just the push of a button once you set up the first time. Then 
            you have the choice to move to the precision alignment point to get it more perfect than homing in no time or if you are experienced 
            and know your printer you can skip straight to resume now.  So the flow is measure, click, click, resume. It is that easy!  And so 
            satisfying to watch that nozzle go right back to the point of failure and continue you might start wanting your prints to fail like me.
            just so to see how fast and accurate it can be.  Any dancing tacos that crap icecream that resemble any other dancing tacos that crap 
            icecream is purely coincidental.  Thanks for having an IQ higher than a potatoe and choosing OctoGoat.  Save time, Save money, Save that 
            print!  And shout out to Creality for making such garabage printers, that by having to rebuid them, gave me the knowledge to make
            OctoGoat possible!.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="modal-footer">
            <button class="btn" type="button" data-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div id="contact-modal"
         class="modal hide fade"
         tabindex="-1"
         role="dialog"
         aria-labelledby="contact-modal-label"
         aria-hidden="true">
        <div class="modal-header">
            <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-hidden="true">&times;</button>
            <h3 id="contact-modal-label">Contact</h3>
        </div>

        <div class="modal-body">
            <p>If you get stuck or have any questions feel free to ask Chat GPT.. that is all I will do.
            Just kidding... kinda ... feel free to contact me at the_real_octogoat@proton.me or 
            ksmith1489@protonmail.com with any questions, interest in collaborations, strategic partnerships,
            or licensing information to use the Lazarus method and system for resuming a failed 
            additive manufacturing in your company's product. Soon to be a standard for all additive 
            manufactoring devices with fully automated upgraded versions already in the works.  
            already in the works. i</p>
        </div>

        <div class="modal-footer">
            <button class="btn" type="button" data-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
